        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 2:39PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 238 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Escalante, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Garfield and northeastern Kane Counties.

This includes Utah Route 12 between mile markers 62 and 71.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Salt Lake City.</instruction>
